                  <handDesc><!--ACHTUNG! first HandNote comes from writing system in Ethiospare. the others are one for each CHANGE OF HAND-->
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre, irregular.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red.</seg>
                        <date>Second half of the 19th century.</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; name of the King; incipit of Text I; incipit of the prayers to be read; directives to the ministers; words yǝbärkäwwo (fols. 5ra-6rb) and nǝsǝʾǝläkä (fols. 18va-19va, 32rb-34ra); elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals. &#xD;
On the incipit page of Text I (fol. 3r), a few lines are rubricated (alternating with black lines).</seg>
                     </handNote>
